## How to run it

1. Open the notebook in [Google Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/)
2. Run all cells in order
3. Download `variant_report.csv` from the Colab file browser

No installation required. All libraries (`requests`, `csv`, `json`, 
`time`, `os`) are built into Python.

## Data sources

| Source | What it provides | Access |
|--------|-----------------|--------|
| [Ensembl REST API](https://rest.ensembl.org) | Chromosome, position, consequence | Free, no login |
| [gnomAD v4](https://gnomad.broadinstitute.org) | Global allele frequency | Free, GraphQL API |

## Rare variant threshold

Variants are flagged as RARE if global gnomAD genome AF < 0.01 (1%).  
This threshold follows ACMG/AMP guidelines for variant interpretation.  
Note: global AF should be interpreted alongside population-specific 
subgroup frequencies, particularly for variants with known 
population stratification (e.g. rs334, HBB sickle cell variant).

